com.moback.android

Class SSOManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.moback.android.SSOManager

  • public class SSOManager
extends Object
    This class provides an interface for single sign-on of users, as well as their registration with MoBack.
    Currently, to use most of the MoBack APIs, there needs to be a user logged in.

        Parameters:
        userID - The user's ID. Frequently, this is the same as the email field.
        email - The user's email.
        password - The user's password.

      • logIn

        public static void logIn(String userName,
         String password,
         BasicCompletionBlock callback)
        Asynchronously logs in a user with the given email and password.
        Parameters:
        userID - The user ID of the user. Typically this is the user's email, but it depends on your setup.
        password - The user's password.
        completion - The completion callback to be used when the user has logged in. Exception if null.
